article.headline: East Tennessee State 71, Radford 51
article.story: JOHNSON CITY, Tenn. (AP) -- Mike Smith scored 16 points and East Tennessee State rallied in the second half for a 71-51 victory Thursday over Radford. ETSU (8-5) trailed 36-33 at the half but went on a 13-2 run to go ahead 48-38 with 12:03 left. The Buccaneers then outscored the Highlanders (5-8) 15-6 in the last six minutes to pull away further. Radford shot just 30.4 percent in the second half while the Bucs hit 50 percent. Andrew Reed added 13 points for ETSU, Courtney Pigram scored 12 and Eryk Thomas 11. Brad Nuckles had 8 points and a game-high 11 rebounds. Amir Johnson led Radford with 13 points, Chris Oliver had 12 and Reggie McIntyre had 10 points and a team-high eight rebounds. Radford made just 1-of-12 3-pointers during the game while the Bucs hit 9-of-22.
